'''Oxford''' can refer to:
==Locations==
* '''[[Oxford]], a city in the Thames Valley in England.'''
** The [[University of Oxford]], [[J.R.R. Tolkien]]'s ''alma mater'' and where he later worked as a professor.
** The [[Oxford English Dictionary]], a publication on which J.R.R. Tolkien worked.
==In Tolkien's Works==
* [[Oxenford]], a city in the [[Little Kingdom]], also in the Thames Valley.
** The [[Four Wise Clerks of Oxenford]], characters from ''[[Farmer Giles of Ham]]''.
==Other Works==
* ''[[Oxford Poetry]]'', an annual book which published several of [[J.R.R. Tolkien]]'s poems
* ''[[Tolkien's Oxford]]'', a [[2008]] book by [[Robert S. Blackham|Bob Blackham]].
* "[[Tolkien in Oxford]]", a documentary.
